HLT-T GroundVehicle/definition description modify "A heavy duty tractor cab variant of the Heavy Lift Tractor capable of hauling a variety of trailers."
HLT-L GroundVehicle/definition description modify "A logistics variant of the Heavy Lift Tractor with a flatbed loading system capable of handling a variety of tasks."
HLT-FT GroundVehicle/definition description modify "A support variant of the Heavy Lift Tractor capable of refueling friendlies nearby."
HLT-M GroundVehicle/definition description modify "A support variant of the Heavy Lift Tractor capable of rearming friendlies nearby. Explodes when hit."
HLT-R GroundVehicle/definition description modify "A mobile radar variant of the Heavy Lift Tractor capable of spotting targets up to 40km away and providing targeting data to nearby surface-to-air missile batteries."
HLT-FC GroundVehicle/definition description modify "A mobile fire control variant of the Heavy Lift Tractor capable of linking with friendly air-defense batteries and providing advanced tracking data and ammunition allocation."
SAMTrailer1 GroundVehicle/definition description modify "A Heavy Lift Tractor compatible trailer with a launch system for R9 StratoLance air-defense missiles, requiring a nearby compatible radar truck for targeting."
CRAMTrailer1 GroundVehicle/definition description modify "A Heavy Lift Tractor compatible trailer with a standalone short-range air-defense system featuring a 20mm rotary cannon, capable of intercepting munitions and shooting down aircraft."
LaserTrailer1 GroundVehicle/definition description modify "A Heavy Lift Tractor compatible trailer with a standalone short-range air-defense system featuring an 80kW pulse laser, capable of intercepting large volleys of light munitions."

Truck2-T GroundVehicle/definition description modify "A heavy duty tractor cab variant of the Modular Support Vehicle capable of hauling a variety of trailers."
Truck2-L GroundVehicle/definition description modify "A logistics variant of the Modular Support Vehicle with a flatbed loading system capable of handling a variety of tasks."
Truck2-FT GroundVehicle/definition description modify "A support variant of the Modular Support Vehicle capable of refueling friendlies nearby."
Truck2-M GroundVehicle/definition description modify "A support variant of the Modular Support Vehicle capable of rearming friendlies nearby. Explodes when hit."
Truck2-R GroundVehicle/definition description modify "A mobile radar variant of the Modular Support Vehicle capable of spotting targets up to 40km away and providing targeting data to nearby surface-to-air missile batteries."
Truck2-FC GroundVehicle/definition description modify "A mobile fire control variant of the Modular Support Vehicle capable of linking with friendly air-defense batteries and providing advanced tracking data and ammunition allocation."
Truck2-RSAM GroundVehicle/definition description modify "A defense variant of the Modular Support Vehicle with a launch system for R9 StratoLance air-defense missiles, requiring a nearby compatible radar truck for targeting."
Truck2-CRAM GroundVehicle/definition description modify "A defense variant of the Modular Support Vehicle with a standalone short-range air-defense system featuring a 20mm rotary cannon, capable of intercepting munitions and shooting down aircraft."
Truck2-LADS GroundVehicle/definition description modify "A defense variant of the Modular Support Vehicle with a standalone short-range air-defense system featuring an 80kW pulse laser, capable of intercepting large volleys of light munitions."
Truck2-TBM GroundVehicle/definition description modify "A strategic variant of the Modular Support Vehicle featuring two vertical launchers for the TBM-3C tactical ballistic missile equipped with a high-explosive warhead. Fires immediately upon reaching the strategic escalation threshold."
Truck2-TBM-N GroundVehicle/definition description modify "A strategic variant of the Modular Support Vehicle featuring two vertical launchers for the TBM-3N tactical ballistic missile equipped with a 20kt nuclear warhead. Fires immediately upon reaching the strategic escalation threshold."

